Content: yeah looks like vardiff puts my z9mini at roughly 4 shares a minute on piratepool.io, thats pretty risky for having a coin that is 60s blocktime. High risk of losing shares. Trying the low diff port for theminingpoolstratum.selfip.com right now and looks much better at around 10 shares a min, but its dropping so i'll see where it equalizes at

Author: CiPhEr#2091
Content: usually 10 to 15 shares a minute is safe (doesn't overly spam pool's network) but reduces chances of losing shares. Basically 1/((accepted shares per min)*(blocktime in minutes of coin)) will give you your % chance of submitting a lost share

Author: CiPhEr#2091
Content: in bitmain asics "utility" = accepted shares per minute and WU = total difficulty submitted. Aim of the game is to adjust difficulty so WU is highest as possible without getting rejected or stale shares.
